    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-04-23T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-04-23T18:00:00-05:00" n="43"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d43">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">883.927/109: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Howell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-04-23T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1926—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. Your 15 April 17, 11 a.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>(1)</label>
                    <item>Metropolitan Museum has communicated to Department texts of cables from
                        Win lock<note n="25" xml:id="d43fn25">Covering letter and texts of cables
                            not printed.</note> reporting that British and French have made
                        representations and that you have presented <hi rend="italic">aide
                            memoire</hi> to Egyptian Foreign Office.<note n="26" xml:id="d43fn26">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_69">p. 69</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>(2)</label>
                    <item>If you have taken reported action you should bear in mind, and if
                        necessary you should orally make it clear to the Egyptian Foreign Office,
                        that this Government hopes that reply to <hi rend="italic">aide memoire</hi>
                        may contain statement from Foreign Office that the Egyptian Government
                        adheres to the principles set forth on page 7 of the Department’s draft
                            note.<note n="27" xml:id="d43fn27">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_62">p. 62</ref>.</note>
                        See Paragraph 3–C of Department’s April 12, 6 p.m. Assurances from the
                        ministry under which Lacau works would not be satisfactory.</item>
                    <label>(3)</label>
                    <item>Report fully by telegraph developments in situation and action taken by
                        you since your April 17, 11 a.m.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
